description: This file is the entry point for a ReactJS web application, setting up the root rendering, providers for state management (Redux), routing (React Router), data fetching (react-query), and toast notifications (react-hot-toast). It initializes the React DOM root and renders the main App component wrapped with necessary providers.

methods.name: ReactDOM.createRoot
methods.description: Creates a root to render a React component tree into the specified DOM element.
